results.name: Each row of triangle T(n,k) has a sorted list of n values such that sigma(T(n,k)) = A007368(n).
comment: The first and last terms of each row are given in A184393 and A184394.
Note that the integers in the 10th row have sigma(n)=504 (A180164(1)) and thus include A002025(1) and A002046(1). - _Michel Marcus_, Oct 22 2013
